---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro'
import CTA from '../components/CTA.astro'
import SectionGlow from '../components/SectionGlow.astro'
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About — Beme"
  description="Why Beme exists, who it's for, and the trade it's built for."
>
  <section class="relative overflow-hidden">
    {/* Amber glow on About — a warmer, story-page feel that
        distinguishes it from the orange-led product pages. */}
    <SectionGlow color="amber" position="top-right" intensity="subtle" />
    <div class="container-tight max-w-3xl mx-auto relative" style="padding-top: clamp(5rem, 7vw, 9rem); padding-bottom: clamp(4rem, 6vw, 6rem);">
    <div class="text-xs uppercase tracking-wider text-beme-400 font-semibold mb-4">
      About
    </div>
    <h1 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold text-ink-50 tracking-tight">
      Built for brick and block. Nothing else.
    </h1>

    <div class="mt-10 space-y-6 text-[17px] text-ink-200 leading-relaxed">
      <p>
        Beme is estimating software built specifically for brick and
        block tradies and the suppliers selling to them. It's not a
        general takeoff tool with a brick mode bolted on the side.
        Every rule, every quirk, every detail a brickie or blocklayer
        knows is built into the software.
      </p>

      <p>
        The schedule matches the build — no rounding, no assumptions.
        Whatever the customer ends up with — schedule, 3D view, PDF —
        is something they can actually read.
      </p>
    </div>

    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-ink-50 mt-14 mb-3">Why it exists</h2>
    <p class="text-[17px] text-ink-200 leading-relaxed">
      Most takeoff tools cover every trade. Powerful, but not made
      for any one of them. Estimating a brick or block wall in a
      general-purpose tool means rebuilding the wall logic from
      scratch every time, in a spreadsheet bolted to the side. Beme
      goes the other way: brick and block, done properly, with the
      bond intelligence, corner logic, and lintel handling that
      general tools never bother with.
    </p>

    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-ink-50 mt-12 mb-3">Who it's for</h2>
    <p class="text-[17px] text-ink-200 leading-relaxed">
      Individual tradies estimating their own jobs. Brick and block
      suppliers using it as part of how they sell — sending customers
      an accurate schedule and a 3D walkthrough back the same day,
      without setting up an estimating team.
    </p>

    <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-ink-50 mt-12 mb-3">Who's behind it</h2>
    <p class="text-[17px] text-ink-200 leading-relaxed">
      Beme is built in Australia. If you've got feedback, found a
      bug, or want a feature added, get in touch at
      <a href="mailto:hello@beme.com.au" class="text-beme-400 hover:text-beme-300 underline">
        hello@beme.com.au
      </a>.
    </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <CTA />
</BaseLayout>
